01 – Host Identification
The investigation began by identifying the internal host 192.168.70.186, which was responsible for initiating the suspicious outbound network communication.

02 – Host Network Activity by Protocol
Network activity generated by the host was analyzed by protocol to determine what types of traffic the system was producing.

03 – Connection Verification
The connection between the internal host 192.168.70.186 and the external IP 45.77.53.176 was confirmed to verify that active communication was occurring.

04 – External IP Analysis
The destination IP address 45.77.53.176 was investigated to determine whether it was associated with suspicious or potentially malicious infrastructure.

05 – Geolocation Analysis of Destination IP
Geolocation analysis was performed on the destination IP to identify the physical region where the remote server was located.

06 – WHOIS Lookup for Destination IP
A WHOIS lookup was conducted to determine the organization and hosting provider responsible for the destination IP address.

07 – DNS Resolution Check for Suspicious IP
DNS activity was examined to determine whether the host attempted to resolve a domain associated with the suspicious IP address.

08 – Protocol Validation
The communication protocol used in the connection was validated to ensure the traffic matched expected protocol behavior.

09 – Destination Port Usage
The destination port used in the connection was analyzed to determine whether the traffic was using common service ports or unusual ports.

10 – Data Transfer Analysis (Bytes Sent vs Received)
The volume of data transmitted between the host and the destination IP was analyzed to assess whether significant data transfer or potential exfiltration occurred.

11 – Event Frequency Timeline
A timeline of connection events was created to visualize how frequently the host communicated with the external IP over time.

12 – Connection Time Interval Analysis
The time intervals between connections were analyzed to determine whether the traffic occurred at consistent or patterned intervals.

13 – Beaconing Detection
The analysis revealed a consistent communication pattern characteristic of beaconing, which is commonly associated with command-and-control activity.

14 - Multi-Host Beaconing Activity
Shows all internal hosts communicating with the suspicious destination IP over time, revealing synchronized beaconing behavior.

15 - Individual Host Beaconing Pattern (192.168.24.128)
Shows the consistent one-minute interval communication pattern from the infected host to the suspected command-and-control server.

16 - Source Host Communication Distribution
Displays which internal hosts are communicating with the destination IP and the total number of connections generated by each host.
